            </div>
            
                
                
            
        </figure></div><p dir="ltr">Ceremony is an extension of Less Than. In the same way that there are people who are vegan or gluten-free, there are many people who are alcohol-free. They are taken aback that options exist and are curated for them. They feel seen.</p><div class="hidden-print asset-breakout-container "><div class="container-breakout ad-col visible-xs"><div class="tnt-ads-container text-center hidden-print hidden-sm hidden-md hidden-lg"><div style="min-height:250px; min-width:300px;" class="tnt-ads dfp-ad" data-dfp-adunit="/8438/enformeva.com/food-and-spirits" data-dfp-custom-pos="article-breakout, stf, btf, 60" id="article-breakout-mobile-3-mobile" data-dfp-size="[[300,250],[320,50],[300,50],[3,1]]" data-lazy="true"></div></div>
    </div></div><p dir="ltr"> </p><h2 dir="ltr">What effects do you hope Less Than and Ceremony have on our communities and culture?</h2><p dir="ltr">We want to change the status quo. We have many people who bring in big-box-store-branded bottles that they refill repeatedly. This is symbolic of disrupting the status quo. We also want to break down the stigma of being sober. For some reason, if you declare you want to be vegetarian or sober, there’s pushback. We’ve made progress in fostering new conversations and reshaping the industry.</p><div class="inline-asset inline-image layout-vertical   tnt-inline-asset tnt-inline-relcontent tnt-inline-image tnt-inline-relation-child tnt-inline-presentation-default tnt-inline-width-full"><figure class="photo layout-vertical hover-expand letterbox-style-default"><span class="expand hidden-print"
            
               data-toggle="modal"
                   data-photo-target=".photo-cef3cd5e-b629-11ee-a33b-f3d7a0542144" 
