            </div>
                
                
            </div>
            
                
                
            
        </figure></div><h2 dir="ltr">How have you been able to expand the businesses’ presence so quickly?</h2><div class="hidden-print asset-breakout-container subscriber-ad"><div class="container-breakout ad-col visible-xs"><div class="tnt-ads-container text-center hidden-print hidden-sm hidden-md hidden-lg"><div style="min-height:250px; min-width:300px;" class="tnt-ads dfp-ad" data-dfp-adunit="/8438/enformeva.com/food-and-spirits" data-dfp-custom-pos="article-breakout, stf, btf, 60" id="article-breakout-mobile-4-mobile" data-dfp-size="[[300,250],[320,50],[300,50],[3,1]]" data-lazy="true"></div></div>
    </div></div><p dir="ltr">Less Than started on the web. Our first brick-and-mortar location was in the Ghent area of Norfolk. We then realized we needed a Virginia Beach store — a person is only going to pass so many stores to get to yours. This was during the pandemic. At the time a lot of businesses were closing down, which created a lot of commercial real estate. But we were an essential business, so we began negotiating leases, and that gave us a foundation to continue expansion.</p><div class="hidden-print asset-breakout-container "><div class="container-breakout ad-col visible-sm"><div class="tnt-ads-container text-center hidden-print hidden-xs"><div style="min-height:90px; min-width:728px;" class="tnt-ads dfp-ad" data-dfp-adunit="/8438/enformeva.com/food-and-spirits" data-dfp-custom-pos="article-breakout, stf, btf, 60" id="article-breakout-tablet-3" data-dfp-size="[[728,90],[3,1]]" data-lazy="true"></div></div>
    </div></div></div><div class="col-md-4 fixed-col-right lee-sticky-container hidden-sm hidden-xs"><div class="lee-sticky-ad"><div class="tnt-ads-container text-center hidden-print "><div style="min-height:600px; min-width:300px;" class="tnt-ads dfp-ad" data-dfp-adunit="/8438/enformeva.com/food-and-spirits" data-dfp-custom-pos="article-big-ad, stf, btf, 70" id="article-big-ad-2" data-dfp-size="[[300,600],[300,250]]" data-lazy="true"></div></div>
    </div></div></div><div class="hidden-print asset-breakout-container  subscriber-ad"><div class="container-breakout ad-col visible-md visible-lg"><div class="tnt-ads-container text-center hidden-print hidden-xs"><div style="min-height:250px; min-width:970px;" class="tnt-ads dfp-ad" data-dfp-adunit="/8438/enformeva.com/food-and-spirits" data-dfp-custom-pos="article-breakout, stf, btf, 60" id="article-breakout-desktop-2" data-dfp-size="[[970,250],[970,90],[728,90],[3,1]]" data-lazy="true"></div></div>
    </div></div><div class="row lee-text-row"><div class="col-md-8 fixed-col-left main-content"><h2 dir="ltr">What is the long-term vision for Less Than and Ceremony?</h2><p dir="ltr">It’s to expand the number of businesses that we have. We can make hubs where we can warehouse goods, ramp up logistics, and create more jobs. For Ceremony, we want to bring in larger quantities and assist anyone who wants to carry non-alcohol options. We are testing a non-alcohol bar and our own non-alcoholic beverage line. We are ready to pivot to build out different facets of zero-waste and zero-proof spaces.</p><div class="clearfix"></div>
    
